Today, we had a great opportunity to rethink malaria elimination in Nigeria. Thanks @DrTedros @WHO @MoetiTshidi, @GlobalFund @PeterASands, @gavi , @drdavidwalton, @PMIgov, @JoyPhumaphi_, Hon Minister of State @DrTunjiAlausa, Dr Ntadom NC NMEP @Fmohnigeria, and numerous Nigerian, African, and global health leaders for joining us to interrogate the facts and begin to chart a new path towards malaria elimination as part of President Tinubuâ€™s @officialABAT Renewed Hope Agenda. We also were glad to have the Nigerian Governors Forum @NGFSecretariat and sub-national leadership in the dialogue.

We identified key shifts and strategic actions to combat malaria in Nigeria, including:

1.Establishing an independent Advisory group on Malaria Elimination in Nigeria (#AMEN);
2.Developing a pragmatic, costed plan for malaria elimination making explicit the required trade offs;
3.Intensified malaria case management, including NHIA reforms, domesticated Affordable Medicines for malaria effort, expanding primary health and frontline workforce;
4.Mobilizing domestic and global funding for malaria;
5. Relentless focus on operational excellence to deploy and optimize existing tools for high coverage, including LLINs, SMC, IPT, IVM and phased introduction of safe, efficacious vaccines;
6.Enhancing community and leadership involvement in malaria elimination;
7.Strengthening data integrity and accountability;
8.Intensifying preparedness and response to climate changeâ€™s impacts on malaria;
9.Exploring bold innovations in service delivery and financing mechanisms.

